# Multi-Agent — REST Client (VS Code: REST Client by Huachao Mao)
# Run worker: npm run worker:multi-agent (from repo root)
# Pattern B: run orchestrator with worker up: npm run orchestrate:multi-agent -- "Your question"

@base = http://localhost:3000
@workflowId = <paste workflowId from start response>

### Start multi-agent workflow — Pattern A (Researcher → Coder → Analyst in one workflow)
POST {{base}}/workflows/start
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "workflowType": "multiAgentWorkflow",
  "input": {
    "query": "What are the main risks of adopting microservices?"
  }
}

### Get run status
GET {{base}}/runs/{{workflowId}}

### Get run result (wait until status is COMPLETED)
GET {{base}}/runs/{{workflowId}}/result
